<section xml:id="csp-name-turtles_turtle-art">
  <title>Turtle Art</title>
  <p>Below is a program to draw a simple house.</p>

  <program xml:id="cspnameturtles_turtleart1" interactive="activecode" language="python">
    <input>
from turtle import *
bob = Turtle()
bob.speed(8)

# Make a square
bob.fillcolor("light yellow")
bob.begin_fill()
bob.forward(100)
bob.right(90)
bob.forward(100)
bob.right(90)
bob.forward(100)
bob.right(90)
bob.forward(100)
bob.end_fill()

# Position for roof
bob.right(90)

# Make a roof
bob.fillcolor("black")
bob.begin_fill()
bob.forward(100)
bob.left(120)
bob.forward(100)
bob.left(120)
bob.forward(100)
bob.left(120)
bob.end_fill()
        </input>
  </program>
  <p>Now we want to add a &#8220;chimney&#8221; to the house that looks something like this:</p>
  <image source="CSPNameTurtles/Figures/turtle-house-3.png" width="20%" />
  <p>Modify the program above so that it draws a <c>"red"</c> chimney. You can either draw it before or after drawing the
    roof.</p>

</section>

